What was derived from TouhouRPC
-------------------------------

The following are ported from TouhouRPC and remain covered by GPL v3:

  * Memory addresses for TH06-TH18 (in src/games.rs)
  * State-machine logic for menu / stage / boss / mid-boss detection
  * Per-stage mid-boss and boss name tables
  * Discord application IDs used to fetch cover art from Discord's CDN

What is original to this project
--------------------------------

The following are original to touhou-rpc-for-linux and are released under GPL v3
because the project as a whole is a derivative work:

  * Native Linux process detection via /proc scanning (src/process.rs)
  * Memory reading via process_vm_readv(2) with /proc/<pid>/mem fallback
    (src/memory.rs)
  * A hand-rolled Discord IPC client speaking directly to the Unix domain
    socket at $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/discord-ipc-* (src/discord.rs), replacing
    TouhouRPC's use of Discord's Windows-only Game SDK DLL
  * The Rust port itself, along with all trait design, snapshot data model,
    per-game reconnect logic, and pid-recycling guards (src/main.rs,
    src/common.rs)

